  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Manufacturing Engineer (Machining)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for creating manufacturing process sequence, from receipt of raw materials till finished parts shipment.</li>\n  <li>In Charge of developing new processes solid modeling and create/update work instructions, in accordance with engineering drawings and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for creating CNC code/program for machining as well as designing toolings, fixtures and gauges.</li>\n  <li>In charge of creating special processes such as Heat Treatment, Brazing, EDM, Shotpeening and Welding etc.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for conducting pre-production pilot run and training for associates.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical support to Production to achieve technical and quality requirements.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in liaising with OEM on product requirements, process qualifications and technology development.</li>\n  <li>Support continuous improvement projects and Request for Quote (RFQ) proposal development and process</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirement</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Degree in Mechanical/Manufacturing/Aeronautical/Material Engineering</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years’ experience in precision engineering in Manufacturing Environment with competent with CAD software;</li>\n  <li>Experience in special processes such as Heat Treatment, Brazing, EDM, Shotpeening and Welding will be advantage</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call <strong>+(65) </strong><a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd<br>\nEA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
